            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-07-03T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-07-03T14:00:00-05:00" n="419" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d419">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">855A.6359/7–347: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-07-03T20:00:00+01:00">July 3, 1947—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1067. For Under Secretary Lovett from Kirk. Have assured Spaak regarding our
                    intention faithfully to implement provisions of paragraph 9A when we are in
                    position to do so. Outlining generally difficulties and possibilities
                    utilization atomic energy for industrial purposes, I found him quite responsive
                    and willing to wait developments. He likewise fully appreciative our problem
                    regarding UN and while somewhat surprised extent Russian <hi rend="italic">intransigeance</hi> yet wholly sympathetic and prepared prevent premature
                    disclosures. He now understands our concern and will play ball.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
